DESCRIPTION:TIDES:\n-0.051ft at 10:12\n-2.925ft at 12:48\n\nOBSERVATION:\n
 Fresh combo of NW swell and new S swell both filling in - the NW swell wil
 l be dominant for most spots. The mix looks good for widespread waist-ches
 t-shoulder high waves by the afternoon\, as better breaks are head high+. 
 \n\nDraining negative low tide first part of the morning\, then incoming t
 ide push helps through mid day. Early afternoon high tide slows tide sensi
 tive spots. Light/variable winds through the morning\, expected to turn li
 ght+ SW onshore for the afternoon. 
END:VEVENT
